not if I have anything to say about it.<br>
This is my point.  They're trying to do this the wrong way. Why are we in such a rush?  What's the hurry?  As long as it is inevitable, which it is, why not do it the RIGHT way.  Do you know how far back the apollo missions set space travel?  If we'd been using RLV's from the beginning (delta clipper?) then the whole thing would have been significantly cheaper.  Instead, we went with what we knew would work... we just scaled up a V-2 and added a crew capsule.  We still put range safety on the shuttle, believe it or not!<br>
(Range safety is basically a holdover from early missile launch technology... it's a bomb on the ship that can be used to blow it to bits if it starts to go off course.  It prevents the vehicle from crashing into a populated area.  The shuttle is the only manned vehicle EVER built with 'range safety')<br>
<br>
The government/militarization of space dramatically restricts private concerns.  The government effectively monopolized space travel for 30 years. If they put another 500 billion into space to get to mars, you can bet that private concerns will be scared of doing it.  <br>
If you heard it took 500 billion to get to mars, why would you even try?<br>
<br>
I also don't want MY TAX Dollars spent that way.  I know there are much better places they could be spent.  There is a lot of money out there for space, and its growing every day.  The pros of government involvement simply don't outweight the cons.<br>
<br>
Please don't take this the wrong way.  It is a personal dream of mine to actually build a vessel and walk on mars.  I'm an Aerospace engineering student and I have evry intention of assisting in the creation of the necessary technology.  But I also have no plans whatsoever to go work for NASA or Lockheed and get handouts of money from the government to do what I want.  I plan to work for it.  It'll be hard, but worth it, in the long run.  I want to do it the right way, so that others can follow along easily. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cotopaxi@nuclearspace>cotopaxi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/12/04 4:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=993.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/16.gif" align=absmiddle>  shut up! and join the TEAM</span><hr size=1> I say...quit the gripes, and whining, go to work and pay your taxes. <br>
